06/05/2005
NIKSIC, Serbia-Montenegro -- Jovanka Karadzic, the mother of former Bosnian Serb leader and war crimes indictee Radovan Karadzic, died Thursday (5 May) in Niksic, Montenegro.
News of her death has triggered a series of events aimed at capturing Karadzic.
Members of his family are being closely watched, since in the past there have been numerous reports of war crimes indictees attending the funerals of relatives.
As the burial site has not been selected, several locations reportedly are under surveillance.
(Dnevni Avaz, Nezavisne Novine - 06/05/05;
BBC, B92 - 05/05/05)
